There has been another roof collapse at the Somerset Mall in Strand, Cape Town's fire and rescue said on Thursday. "There was a roof collapse," said Cape Town's fire and rescue spokesperson Jermaine Carelse. It is understood to have occurred in the area of Wimpy and Clicks. Further details were not immediately available. In 2018, one person was injured after a part of the roof collapsed. The mall is expected to comment on the incident shortly.  The mall is
expected to comment on the incident shortly. The mall
houses numerous retail brands and its website blurb promises "a safe,
'fun-filled entertainment environment'. " At the time
of the 2018 collapse, a precautionary audit on the structure was conducted. The injury
sustained in that collapse was attributed to a person tripping while running
for safety.  SOURCE: NEWS24